# Nightshift Kit — Ephemeral Files

# Do NOT track these files. They are generated during nightshift runs and should not be versioned.

# Metrics being written (finalized metrics are in metrics/*.yaml and ARE tracked)
metrics/_wip/*

# Reports being written (finalized reports are in reports/*.md and ARE tracked)
reports/_wip/*

# Async reflection outputs (ephemeral, like .argo/)
reflections/*

# Manual stop signal file
STOP

# Dynamic timeout history (auto-generated by timed_run.py)
timings.json

# Temporary work files (if agent creates any)
*.tmp
.DS_Store

---

# Files THAT SHOULD BE TRACKED:

# ✅ Protocol files (the loop itself)
# - LOOP.md
# - REVIEW.md
# - BOOTSTRAP.md
# - HUMAN-REVIEW.md
# - WATCHER.md
# - config.yaml

# ✅ Input (specs)
# - specs/*.md (all spec files)

# ✅ Knowledge (learned patterns)
# - knowledge/*.md (accumulated project wisdom)

# ✅ Output (metrics and reports)
# - metrics/*.yaml (structured telemetry)
# - reports/*.md (human-readable summaries)

# ✅ Templates
# - specs/_TEMPLATE.md
# - metrics/_SCHEMA.md (if created)

# ✅ .gitkeep (directory markers)
# - reports/.gitkeep
# - metrics/.gitkeep
# - knowledge/.gitkeep

---

# Notes

# Worktree directories are created OUTSIDE the project root
# (as siblings, named {project}-ns-SPEC-001, etc.)
# Git handles them correctly by default. No need to gitignore.

# If using standalone branches instead of worktrees:
# - Branches are tracked normally
# - No gitignore needed for them
